      "content": "Taking 50,000 IU daily without blood monitoring is dangerous because kidney stones and hypercalcemia (dangerously high calcium) can develop too quickly, regardless of taking Calcium and Vitamin K. Symptoms of toxicity often appear within days, including nausea, confusion, and extreme fatigue, which worsen your feeling of being \"run down\" you already experience. Because your body cannot filter excess vitamin D fast enough, a month of this dosage could actually harm your kidneys before you feel better. Please see a doctor immediately for a supervised plan, as self-treating such a high risk is never safe.",
